171
00:18:11,600 --> 00:18:15,000
It's okay. Just give them to him when you see him.

172
00:18:18,800 --> 00:18:24,300
I'll take the day off to take care of something.

173
00:18:27,100 --> 00:18:28,900
Chen Guangpu.

174
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:37,700
Tell Lin Tuo that I'll wait for him at HW Cafe tonight.

175
00:18:40,800 --> 00:18:42,400
Okay.

176
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:53,500
It's okay.

177
00:18:53,500 --> 00:18:55,000
Come on.

178
00:18:56,600 --> 00:19:00,300
  . 

179
00:19:06,400 --> 00:19:08,400
Which one do you like?

180
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:11,800
I like this one.

181
00:19:13,100 --> 00:19:14,800
Why?

182
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:16,900
It's practical and cost-effective.

183
00:19:16,900 --> 00:19:21,500
There aren't so many fancy things in the materials and design.

184
00:19:21,500 --> 00:19:25,200
Good. You've learned well and grasped the essence of it.

185
00:19:25,900 --> 00:19:29,300
Are these all your drawings?

186
00:19:29,300 --> 00:19:32,200
They were designed years ago and not perfect.

187
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:34,600
Do you want to improve them together?

188
00:19:38,600 --> 00:19:43,200
Are you giving me these, so I can just use them?

189
00:19:43,200 --> 00:19:47,200
I'm not that great. Why would I give you my drawings?

190
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:51,600
You are my assistant. It's your job to help me improve.

191
00:19:51,600 --> 00:19:54,200
It's not time for you to categorize them.

192
00:19:58,600 --> 00:20:00,370
Lin Tuo.

193
00:20:01,940 --> 00:20:04,000
There's still time, right?

194
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:06,100
Yes.

195
00:20:06,100 --> 00:20:08,200
Then don't waste it.

196
